terms.medium_def:
A king of Judah living at the time of Divided Monarchy, first mentioned at 2Ki.24.17; 
referred to as Zedekiah (צִדְקִיָּ֫הוּ), or Mattaniah (מַתַּנְיָ֫הוּ); 
son of Josiah and Hamutal; 
a brother of Jehoahaz; 
half-brother of: Jehoiakim and Shallum.

A High Priest from the tribe of Levi living at the time of United Monarchy, first mentioned at 2Sa.8.17; 
only referred to as Zadok (צָדוֹק); 
a son of Ahitub; 
father of Ahimaaz.

A High Priest from the tribe of Levi living at the time of Divided Monarchy, first mentioned at 1Ch.6.12; 
only referred to as Zadok (צָדוֹק); 
a son of Ahitub; 
father of Shallum.

A man living at the time of Divided Monarchy, first mentioned at 1Ki.22.11; 
only referred to as Zedekiah (צִדְקִיָּ֫הוּ); 
a son of Chenaanah.

A man living at the time of Divided Monarchy, first mentioned at 2Ki.15.33; 
only referred to as Zadok (צָדוֹק); 
father of Jerusha.

A man living at the time of Divided Monarchy, first mentioned at Jer.29.21; 
only referred to as Zedekiah (צִדְקִיָּ֫הוּ); 
a son of Maaseiah.

A man living at the time of Exile and Return, only mentioned at Neh.3.4; 
only referred to as Zadok (צָדוֹק); 
a son of Baana.

A man living at the time of Exile and Return, only mentioned at Neh.3.29; 
only referred to as Zadok (צָדוֹק); 
a son of Immer.

A man from the tribe of Judah living at the time of Divided Monarchy, only mentioned at 1Ch.3.16; 
only referred to as Zedekiah (צִדְקִיָּ֫הוּ); 
son of Jehoiachin; 
a brother of Shealtiel.

A man living at the time of Divided Monarchy, only mentioned at Jer.36.12; 
only referred to as Zedekiah (צִדְקִיָּ֫הוּ); 
a son of Hananiah.
